      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Tranexamic acid, a drug useful against blood clotting, is prepared commercially from <i>p</i>-methylbenzonitrile. Formulate the steps likely to be used in the synthesis. (Don’t worry about cis–trans isomers; heating to 300 °C interconverts the isomers.)</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBazRYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--10eda77abc2d52e948b3f1637e51635a9f702ad9/OChem_21_EC_055.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of tranexamic acid comprises of a cyclohexane ring wedge-bonded to a carboxylic acid group and dash-bonded to hydrogen at C 1, and wedge-bonded to hydrogen and dash-bonded to methylamine at C 4.\">",
